3458 void MacroAssembler::TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimizationAndJump(
3459  Register code_data_container, Register scratch, Condition cond,
3460  Label* target) {
3461  Ld_wu(scratch, FieldMemOperand(code_data_container, Code::kFlagsOffset));
3462  And(scratch, scratch, Operand(1 << Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit));
3463  Branch(target, cond, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
3464 }

3468 }
3469 
3470 void MacroAssembler::InvokePrologue(Register expected_parameter_count,
3471  Register actual_parameter_count,
3472  InvokeType type) {
3473  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3474  Label regular_invoke;
3475 
3476  // a0: actual arguments count
3477  // a1: function (passed through to callee)
3478  // a2: expected arguments count
3479 
3480  DCHECK_EQ(actual_parameter_count, a0);
3481  DCHECK_EQ(expected_parameter_count, a2);
3482 
3483  // If overapplication or if the actual argument count is equal to the
3484  // formal parameter count, no need to push extra undefined values.
3485  sub_d(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count,
3486  actual_parameter_count);
3487  Branch(&regular_invoke, le, expected_parameter_count, Operand(zero_reg));
3488 
3489  Label stack_overflow;
3490  StackOverflowCheck(expected_parameter_count, t0, t1, &stack_overflow);
3491  // Underapplication. Move the arguments already in the stack, including the
3492  // receiver and the return address.
3493  {
3494  Label copy;
3495  Register src = a6, dest = a7;
3496  mov(src, sp);
3497  slli_d(t0, expected_parameter_count, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
3498  Sub_d(sp, sp, Operand(t0));
3499  // Update stack pointer.
3500  mov(dest, sp);
3501  mov(t0, actual_parameter_count);
3502  bind(&copy);
3503  Ld_d(t1, MemOperand(src, 0));
3504  St_d(t1, MemOperand(dest, 0));
3505  Sub_d(t0, t0, Operand(1));
3506  Add_d(src, src, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
3507  Add_d(dest, dest, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
3508  Branch(&copy, gt, t0, Operand(zero_reg));
3509  }
3510 
3511  // Fill remaining expected arguments with undefined values.
3512  LoadRoot(t0, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
3513  {
3514  Label loop;
3515  bind(&loop);
3516  St_d(t0, MemOperand(a7, 0));
3517  Sub_d(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count, Operand(1));
3518  Add_d(a7, a7, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
3519  Branch(&loop, gt, expected_parameter_count, Operand(zero_reg));
3520  }
3521  b(&regular_invoke);
3522 
3523  bind(&stack_overflow);
3524  {
3525  FrameScope frame(
3526  this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
3527  CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
3528  break_(0xCC);
3529  }
3530 
3531  bind(&regular_invoke);
3532 }
3533 
3534 void MacroAssembler::CallDebugOnFunctionCall(
3535  Register fun, Register new_target,
3536  Register expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle,
3537  Register actual_parameter_count) {
3538  DCHECK(!AreAliased(t0, fun, new_target,
3539  expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle,
3540  actual_parameter_count));
3541  // Load receiver to pass it later to DebugOnFunctionCall hook.
3542  LoadReceiver(t0);
3543  FrameScope frame(
3544  this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
3545 
3546  SmiTag(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
3547  SmiTag(actual_parameter_count);
3548  Push(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle, actual_parameter_count);
3549 
3550  if (new_target.is_valid()) {
3551  Push(new_target);
3552  }
3553  Push(fun, fun, t0);
3554  CallRuntime(Runtime::kDebugOnFunctionCall);
3555  Pop(fun);
3556  if (new_target.is_valid()) {
3557  Pop(new_target);
3558  }
3559 
3560  Pop(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle, actual_parameter_count);
3561  SmiUntag(actual_parameter_count);
3562  SmiUntag(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
3563 }

3567  Register function, Register actual_parameter_count, InvokeType type,
3568  ArgumentAdaptionMode argument_adaption_mode) {
3569  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3570  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
3571  DCHECK(type == InvokeType::kJump || has_frame());
3572 
3573  // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
3574  // (See FullCodeGenerator::Generate().)
3575  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
3576 
3577  // Set up the context.
3578  LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
3579 
3580  InvokeFunctionCode(function, no_reg, actual_parameter_count, type,
3581  argument_adaption_mode);
3582 }

3589  DCHECK(type == InvokeType::kJump || has_frame());

3599 
3600 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(
3601  Register function, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
3602  InvokeType type, ArgumentAdaptionMode argument_adaption_mode) {
3603  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3604  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
3605  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
3606  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
3607  DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == a3);
3608 
3609  Register dispatch_handle = kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister;
3610  Ld_w(dispatch_handle,
3611  FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
3612 
3613  // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
3614  Label debug_hook, continue_after_hook;
3615  {
3616  li(t0, ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate()));
3617  Ld_b(t0, MemOperand(t0, 0));
3618  BranchShort(&debug_hook, ne, t0, Operand(zero_reg));
3619  }
3620  bind(&continue_after_hook);
3621 
3622  // Clear the new.target register if not given.
3623  if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
3624  LoadRoot(a3, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
3625  }
3626 
3627  Register scratch = s1;
3628  if (argument_adaption_mode == ArgumentAdaptionMode::kAdapt) {
3629  Register expected_parameter_count = a2;
3630  LoadParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(expected_parameter_count,
3631  dispatch_handle, scratch);
3632  InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, type);
3633  }
3634 
3635  // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
3636  // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
3637  // call sites.
3638  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister,
3639  dispatch_handle, scratch);
3640  switch (type) {
3641  case InvokeType::kCall:
3642  Call(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
3643  break;
3644  case InvokeType::kJump:
3645  Jump(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
3646  break;
3647  }
3648  Label done;
3649  Branch(&done);
3650 
3651  // Deferred debug hook.
3652  bind(&debug_hook);
3653  CallDebugOnFunctionCall(function, new_target, dispatch_handle,
3654  actual_parameter_count);
3655  Branch(&continue_after_hook);
3656 
3657  bind(&done);
3658 }
3659 #else
3660 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(Register function, Register new_target,
3661  Register expected_parameter_count,
3662  Register actual_parameter_count,
3663  InvokeType type) {
3664  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
3665  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
3666  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
3667  DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == a3);
3668 
3669  // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
3670  Label debug_hook, continue_after_hook;
3671  {
3672  li(t0, ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate()));
3673  Ld_b(t0, MemOperand(t0, 0));
3674  BranchShort(&debug_hook, ne, t0, Operand(zero_reg));
3675  }
3676  bind(&continue_after_hook);
3677 
3678  // Clear the new.target register if not given.
3679  if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
3680  LoadRoot(a3, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
3681  }
3682 
3683  InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, type);
3684 
3685  // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
3686  // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
3687  // call sites.
3688  constexpr int unused_argument_count = 0;
3689  switch (type) {
3690  case InvokeType::kCall:
3691  CallJSFunction(function, unused_argument_count);
3692  break;
3693  case InvokeType::kJump:
3694  JumpJSFunction(function);
3695  break;
3696  }
3697 
3698  Label done;
3699  Branch(&done);
3700 
3701  // Deferred debug hook.
3702  bind(&debug_hook);
3703  CallDebugOnFunctionCall(function, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
3704  actual_parameter_count);
3705  Branch(&continue_after_hook);
3706 
3707  // Continue here if InvokePrologue does handle the invocation due to
3708  // mismatched parameter counts.
3709  bind(&done);
3710 }
3711 
3712 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionWithNewTarget(
3713  Register function, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
3714  InvokeType type) {
3715  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3716  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
3717  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
3718 
3719  // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
3720  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
3721  Register expected_parameter_count = a2;
3722  Register temp_reg = t0;
3723  LoadTaggedField(temp_reg,
3724  FieldMemOperand(a1, JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset));
3725  LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(a1, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
3726  // The argument count is stored as uint16_t
3727  Ld_hu(expected_parameter_count,
3728  FieldMemOperand(temp_reg,
3729  SharedFunctionInfo::kFormalParameterCountOffset));
3730 
3731  InvokeFunctionCode(a1, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
3732  actual_parameter_count, type);
3733 }

3735 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunction(Register function,
3736  Register expected_parameter_count,
3737  Register actual_parameter_count,
3738  InvokeType type) {
3739  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3740  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
3741  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
3742 
3743  // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
3744  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
3745 
3746  // Get the function and setup the context.
3747  LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(a1, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
3748 
3749  InvokeFunctionCode(a1, no_reg, expected_parameter_count,
3750  actual_parameter_count, type);
3751 }

3775 void MacroAssembler::AddOverflow_d(Register dst, Register left,
3776  const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
3777  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3778  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3779  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3780  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3781  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
3782  Register right_reg = no_reg;
3783  if (!right.is_reg()) {
3784  li(scratch, Operand(right));
3785  right_reg = scratch;
3786  } else {
3787  right_reg = right.rm();
3788  }
3789 
3790  DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
3791  overflow != scratch2);
3792  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
3793 
3794  if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
3795  add_d(scratch2, left, right_reg);
3796  xor_(overflow, scratch2, left);
3797  xor_(scratch, scratch2, right_reg);
3798  and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
3799  mov(dst, scratch2);
3800  } else {
3801  add_d(dst, left, right_reg);
3802  xor_(overflow, dst, left);
3803  xor_(scratch, dst, right_reg);
3804  and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
3805  }
3806 }
3807 
3808 void MacroAssembler::SubOverflow_d(Register dst, Register left,
3809  const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
3810  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3811  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3812  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3813  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3814  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
3815  Register right_reg = no_reg;
3816  if (!right.is_reg()) {
3817  li(scratch, Operand(right));
3818  right_reg = scratch;
3819  } else {
3820  right_reg = right.rm();
3821  }
3822 
3823  DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
3824  overflow != scratch2);
3825  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
3826 
3827  if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
3828  Sub_d(scratch2, left, right_reg);
3829  xor_(overflow, left, scratch2);
3830  xor_(scratch, left, right_reg);
3831  and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
3832  mov(dst, scratch2);
3833  } else {
3834  sub_d(dst, left, right_reg);
3835  xor_(overflow, left, dst);
3836  xor_(scratch, left, right_reg);
3837  and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
3838  }
3839 }

3841 void MacroAssembler::MulOverflow_w(Register dst, Register left,
3842  const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
3843  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3844  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3845  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3846  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3847  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
3848  Register right_reg = no_reg;
3849  if (!right.is_reg()) {
3850  li(scratch, Operand(right));
3851  right_reg = scratch;
3852  } else {
3853  right_reg = right.rm();
3854  }
3855 
3856  DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
3857  overflow != scratch2);
3858  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
3859 
3860  if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
3861  Mul_w(scratch2, left, right_reg);
3862  Mulh_w(overflow, left, right_reg);
3863  mov(dst, scratch2);
3864  } else {
3865  Mul_w(dst, left, right_reg);
3866  Mulh_w(overflow, left, right_reg);
3867  }
3868 
3869  srai_d(scratch2, dst, 32);
3870  xor_(overflow, overflow, scratch2);
3871 }

3905 void MacroAssembler::CallRuntime(const Runtime::Function* f,
3906  int num_arguments) {
3907  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3908  // All parameters are on the stack. v0 has the return value after call.
3909 
3910  // If the expected number of arguments of the runtime function is
3911  // constant, we check that the actual number of arguments match the
3912  // expectation.
3913  CHECK(f->nargs < 0 || f->nargs == num_arguments);
3914 
3915  // TODO(1236192): Most runtime routines don't need the number of
3916  // arguments passed in because it is constant. At some point we
3917  // should remove this need and make the runtime routine entry code
3918  // smarter.
3919  PrepareCEntryArgs(num_arguments);
3920  PrepareCEntryFunction(ExternalReference::Create(f));
3921  bool switch_to_central_stack = options().is_wasm;
3922  CallBuiltin(Builtins::RuntimeCEntry(f->result_size, switch_to_central_stack));
3923 }
3924 
3925 void MacroAssembler::TailCallRuntime(Runtime::FunctionId fid) {
3926  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3927  const Runtime::Function* function = Runtime::FunctionForId(fid);
3928  DCHECK_EQ(1, function->result_size);
3929  if (function->nargs >= 0) {
3930  PrepareCEntryArgs(function->nargs);
3931  }
3932  JumpToExternalReference(ExternalReference::Create(fid));
3933 }
3934 
3935 void MacroAssembler::JumpToExternalReference(const ExternalReference& builtin,
3936  bool builtin_exit_frame) {
3937  PrepareCEntryFunction(builtin);
3938  TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::CEntry(1, ArgvMode::kStack, builtin_exit_frame));
3939 }

3941 void MacroAssembler::LoadWeakValue(Register out, Register in,
3942  Label* target_if_cleared) {
3943  CompareTaggedAndBranch(target_if_cleared, eq, in,
3944  Operand(kClearedWeakHeapObjectLower32));
3945  And(out, in, Operand(~kWeakHeapObjectMask));
3946 }

3948 void MacroAssembler::EmitIncrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
3949  Register scratch1,
3950  Register scratch2) {
3951  DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
3952  if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
3953  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3954  // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
3955  // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t dummy_stats_counter_
3956  // field.
3957  li(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
3958  Ld_w(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2, 0));
3959  Add_w(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(value));
3960  St_w(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2, 0));
3961  }
3962 }
3963 
3964 void MacroAssembler::EmitDecrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
3965  Register scratch1,
3966  Register scratch2) {
3967  DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
3968  if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
3969  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3970  // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
3971  // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t dummy_stats_counter_
3972  // field.
3973  li(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
3974  Ld_w(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2, 0));
3975  Sub_w(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(value));
3976  St_w(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2, 0));
3977  }
3978 }

3987  Operand rk) {

3999 
4000 void MacroAssembler::Abort(AbortReason reason) {
4001  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4002  if (v8_flags.code_comments) {
4003  RecordComment("Abort message:", SourceLocation{});
4004  RecordComment(GetAbortReason(reason), SourceLocation{});
4005  }
4006 
4007  // Without debug code, save the code size and just trap.
4008  if (!v8_flags.debug_code || v8_flags.trap_on_abort) {
4009  stop();
4010  return;
4011  }
4012 
4013  if (should_abort_hard()) {
4014  // We don't care if we constructed a frame. Just pretend we did.
4015  FrameScope assume_frame(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
4016  PrepareCallCFunction(1, a0);
4017  li(a0, Operand(static_cast<int>(reason)));
4018  li(a1, ExternalReference::abort_with_reason());
4019  // Use Call directly to avoid any unneeded overhead. The function won't
4020  // return anyway.
4021  Call(a1);
4022  return;
4023  }
4024 
4025  Label abort_start;
4026  bind(&abort_start);
4027 
4028  Move(a0, Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(reason)));
4029 
4030  {
4031  // We don't actually want to generate a pile of code for this, so just
4032  // claim there is a stack frame, without generating one.
4033  FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
4034  if (root_array_available()) {
4035  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4036  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4037  // Generate an indirect call via builtins entry table here in order to
4038  // ensure that the interpreter_entry_return_pc_offset is the same for
4039  // InterpreterEntryTrampoline and InterpreterEntryTrampolineForProfiling
4040  // when v8_flags.debug_code is enabled.
4041  LoadEntryFromBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort, scratch);
4042  Call(scratch);
4043  } else {
4044  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort);
4045  }
4046  }
4047 
4048  // Will not return here.
4049  if (is_trampoline_pool_blocked()) {
4050  // If the calling code cares about the exact number of
4051  // instructions generated, we insert padding here to keep the size
4052  // of the Abort macro constant.
4053  // Currently in debug mode with debug_code enabled the number of
4054  // generated instructions is 10, so we use this as a maximum value.
4055  static const int kExpectedAbortInstructions = 10;
4056  int abort_instructions = InstructionsGeneratedSince(&abort_start);
4057  DCHECK_LE(abort_instructions, kExpectedAbortInstructions);
4058  while (abort_instructions++ < kExpectedAbortInstructions) {
4059  nop();
4060  }
4061  }
4062 }
4063 
4064 void MacroAssembler::LoadMap(Register destination, Register object) {
4065  LoadTaggedField(destination, FieldMemOperand(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
4066 }
4067 
4068 void MacroAssembler::LoadCompressedMap(Register dst, Register object) {

4070  Ld_w(dst, FieldMemOperand(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
4071 }
4072 
4073 void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVector(Register dst, Register closure,
4074  Register scratch, Label* fbv_undef) {
4075  Label done;
4076  // Load the feedback vector from the closure.
4077  LoadTaggedField(dst,
4078  FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kFeedbackCellOffset));
4079  LoadTaggedField(dst, FieldMemOperand(dst, FeedbackCell::kValueOffset));
4080 
4081  // Check if feedback vector is valid.
4082  LoadTaggedField(scratch, FieldMemOperand(dst, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
4083  Ld_hu(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
4084  Branch(&done, eq, scratch, Operand(FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE));
4085 
4086  // Not valid, load undefined.
4087  LoadRoot(dst, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4088  Branch(fbv_undef);
4089 
4090  bind(&done);
4091 }

4098  LoadTaggedField(dst, MemOperand(dst, Context::SlotOffset(index)));

4110 void MacroAssembler::EnterFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
4111  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4112  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4113  Push(ra, fp);
4114  Move(fp, sp);
4115  if (!StackFrame::IsJavaScript(type)) {
4116  li(kScratchReg, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(type)));
4117  Push(kScratchReg);
4118  }
4119 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4120  if (type == StackFrame::WASM || type == StackFrame::WASM_LIFTOFF_SETUP) {
4121  Push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
4122  }
4123 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4124 }
4125 
4126 void MacroAssembler::LeaveFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
4127  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4128  addi_d(sp, fp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
4129  Ld_d(ra, MemOperand(fp, 1 * kSystemPointerSize));
4130  Ld_d(fp, MemOperand(fp, 0 * kSystemPointerSize));
4131 }
4132 
4133 void MacroAssembler::EnterExitFrame(Register scratch, int stack_space,
4134  StackFrame::Type frame_type) {
4135  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4136  DCHECK(frame_type == StackFrame::EXIT ||
4137  frame_type == StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT ||
4138  frame_type == StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT ||
4139  frame_type == StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT);
4140 
4141  using ER = ExternalReference;
4142 
4143  // Set up the frame structure on the stack.
4144  static_assert(2 * kSystemPointerSize ==
4145  ExitFrameConstants::kCallerSPDisplacement);
4146  static_assert(1 * kSystemPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset);
4147  static_assert(0 * kSystemPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset);
4148 
4149  // This is how the stack will look:
4150  // fp + 2 (==kCallerSPDisplacement) - old stack's end
4151  // [fp + 1 (==kCallerPCOffset)] - saved old ra
4152  // [fp + 0 (==kCallerFPOffset)] - saved old fp
4153  // [fp - 1 frame_type Smi
4154  // [fp - 2 (==kSPOffset)] - sp of the called function
4155  // fp - (2 + stack_space + alignment) == sp == [fp - kSPOffset] - top of the
4156  // new stack (will contain saved ra)
4157 
4158  // Save registers and reserve room for saved entry sp.
4159  addi_d(sp, sp,
4160  -2 * kSystemPointerSize - ExitFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp);
4161  St_d(ra, MemOperand(sp, 3 * kSystemPointerSize));
4162  St_d(fp, MemOperand(sp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize));
4163  li(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(frame_type)));
4164  St_d(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 1 * kSystemPointerSize));
4165 
4166  // Set up new frame pointer.
4167  addi_d(fp, sp, ExitFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp);
4168 
4169  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4170  St_d(zero_reg, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
4171  }
4172 
4173  // Save the frame pointer and the context in top.
4174  ER c_entry_fp_address =
4175  ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
4176  St_d(fp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address, no_reg));
4177 
4178  ER context_address = ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
4179  St_d(cp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
4180 
4181  const int frame_alignment = MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment();
4182 
4183  // Reserve place for the return address, stack space and align the frame
4184  // preparing for calling the runtime function.
4185  DCHECK_GE(stack_space, 0);
4186  Sub_d(sp, sp, Operand((stack_space + 1) * kSystemPointerSize));
4187  if (frame_alignment > 0) {
4188  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
4189  And(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_alignment)); // Align stack.
4190  }
4191 
4192  // Set the exit frame sp value to point just before the return address
4193  // location.
4194  addi_d(scratch, sp, kSystemPointerSize);
4195  St_d(scratch, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
4196 }
4197 
4198 void MacroAssembler::LeaveExitFrame(Register scratch) {
4199  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4200  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4201 
4202  using ER = ExternalReference;
4203 
4204  // Restore current context from top and clear it in debug mode.
4205  ER context_address = ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
4206  Ld_d(cp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
4207 
4208  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4209  li(scratch, Operand(Context::kNoContext));
4210  St_d(scratch, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
4211  }
4212 
4213  // Clear the top frame.
4214  ER c_entry_fp_address =
4215  ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
4216  St_d(zero_reg, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address, no_reg));
4217 
4218  // Pop the arguments, restore registers, and return.
4219  mov(sp, fp); // Respect ABI stack constraint.
4220  Ld_d(fp, MemOperand(sp, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset));
4221  Ld_d(ra, MemOperand(sp, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset));
4222  addi_d(sp, sp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
4223 }
4224 
4225 int MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment() {
4226 #if V8_HOST_ARCH_LOONG64
4227  // Running on the real platform. Use the alignment as mandated by the local
4228  // environment.
4229  // Note: This will break if we ever start generating snapshots on one LOONG64
4230  // platform for another LOONG64 platform with a different alignment.
4231  return base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
4232 #else // V8_HOST_ARCH_LOONG64
4233  // If we are using the simulator then we should always align to the expected
4234  // alignment. As the simulator is used to generate snapshots we do not know
4235  // if the target platform will need alignment, so this is controlled from a
4236  // flag.
4237  return v8_flags.sim_stack_alignment;
4238 #endif // V8_HOST_ARCH_LOONG64
4239 }

4241 void MacroAssembler::SmiUntag(Register dst, const MemOperand& src) {
4242  if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
4243  Ld_w(dst, MemOperand(src.base(), SmiWordOffset(src.offset())));
4244  } else {
4245  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
4246  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
4247  Ld_w(dst, src);
4248  } else {
4249  Ld_d(dst, src);
4250  }
4251  SmiUntag(dst);
4252  }
4253 }

4271 void MacroAssembler::JumpIfObjectType(Label* target, Condition cc,
4272  Register object,
4273  InstanceType instance_type,
4274  Register scratch) {
4275  DCHECK(cc == eq || cc == ne);
4276  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4277  if (scratch == no_reg) {
4278  scratch = temps.Acquire();
4279  }
4280  if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL) {
4281  if (std::optional<RootIndex> expected =
4282  InstanceTypeChecker::UniqueMapOfInstanceType(instance_type)) {
4283  Tagged_t ptr = ReadOnlyRootPtr(*expected);
4284  LoadCompressedMap(scratch, object);
4285  Branch(target, cc, scratch, Operand(ptr));
4286  return;
4287  }
4288  }
4289  GetObjectType(object, scratch, scratch);
4290  Branch(target, cc, scratch, Operand(instance_type));
4291 }

4293 void MacroAssembler::JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(Register heap_object,
4294  Register scratch, Label* target,
4295  Label::Distance distance,
4296  Condition cc) {
4297  CHECK(cc == Condition::kUnsignedLessThan ||
4298  cc == Condition::kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual);
4299  if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL) {
4300 #ifdef DEBUG
4301  Label ok;
4302  LoadMap(scratch, heap_object);
4303  GetInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE, scratch);
4304  Branch(&ok, Condition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual, scratch,
4305  Operand(LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE - FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
4306 
4307  LoadMap(scratch, heap_object);
4308  GetInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, FIRST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE,
4309  scratch);
4310  Branch(&ok, Condition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual, scratch,
4311  Operand(LAST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE -
4312  FIRST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE));
4313 
4314  Abort(AbortReason::kInvalidReceiver);
4315  bind(&ok);
4316 #endif // DEBUG
4317 
4318  // All primitive object's maps are allocated at the start of the read only
4319  // heap. Thus JS_RECEIVER's must have maps with larger (compressed)
4320  // addresses.
4321  LoadCompressedMap(scratch, heap_object);
4322  Branch(target, cc, scratch,
4323  Operand(InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit));
4324  } else {
4325  static_assert(LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE == LAST_TYPE);
4326  GetObjectType(heap_object, scratch, scratch);
4327  Branch(target, cc, scratch, Operand(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
4328  }
4329 }

4338 void MacroAssembler::AssertJSAny(Register object, Register map_tmp,
4339  Register tmp, AbortReason abort_reason) {
4340  if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
4341 
4342  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4343  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, map_tmp, tmp));
4344  Label ok;
4345 
4346  JumpIfSmi(object, &ok);
4347 
4348  GetObjectType(object, map_tmp, tmp);
4349 
4350  Branch(&ok, kUnsignedLessThanEqual, tmp, Operand(LAST_NAME_TYPE));
4351 
4352  Branch(&ok, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual, tmp, Operand(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
4353 
4354  Branch(&ok, kEqual, map_tmp, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
4355 
4356  Branch(&ok, kEqual, map_tmp, RootIndex::kBigIntMap);
4357 
4358  Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4359 
4360  Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
4361 
4362  Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
4363 
4364  Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kNullValue);
4365 
4366  Abort(abort_reason);
4367  bind(&ok);
4368 }

4390 void MacroAssembler::AssertStackIsAligned() {
4391  if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
4392  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4393  const int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
4394  const int frame_alignment_mask = frame_alignment - 1;
4395 
4396  if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
4397  Label alignment_as_expected;
4398  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
4399  {
4400  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4401  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4402  andi(scratch, sp, frame_alignment_mask);
4403  Branch(&alignment_as_expected, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
4404  }
4405  // Don't use Check here, as it will call Runtime_Abort re-entering here.
4406  stop();
4407  bind(&alignment_as_expected);
4408  }
4409 }

4424  And(scratch, scratch, Operand(Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit::kMask));
4425  Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAConstructor, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));

4502 void MacroAssembler::AssertUndefinedOrAllocationSite(Register object,
4503  Register scratch) {

4597 
4598 int MacroAssembler::CalculateStackPassedWords(int num_reg_arguments,
4599  int num_double_arguments) {
4600  int stack_passed_words = 0;
4601 
4602  // Up to eight simple arguments are passed in registers a0..a7.
4603  if (num_reg_arguments > kRegisterPassedArguments) {
4604  stack_passed_words += num_reg_arguments - kRegisterPassedArguments;
4605  }
4606  if (num_double_arguments > kFPRegisterPassedArguments) {
4607  int num_count = num_double_arguments - kFPRegisterPassedArguments;
4608  if (num_reg_arguments >= kRegisterPassedArguments) {
4609  stack_passed_words += num_count;
4610  } else if (num_count > kRegisterPassedArguments - num_reg_arguments) {
4611  stack_passed_words +=
4612  num_count - (kRegisterPassedArguments - num_reg_arguments);
4613  }
4614  }
4615  return stack_passed_words;
4616 }
4617 
4618 void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
4619  int num_double_arguments,
4620  Register scratch) {
4621  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4622  int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
4623 
4624  // Up to eight simple arguments in a0..a3, a4..a7, No argument slots.
4625  // Remaining arguments are pushed on the stack.
4626  int stack_passed_arguments =
4627  CalculateStackPassedWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
4628  if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
4629  // Make stack end at alignment and make room for num_arguments - 4 words
4630  // and the original value of sp.
4631  mov(scratch, sp);
4632  Sub_d(sp, sp, Operand((stack_passed_arguments + 1) * kSystemPointerSize));
4633  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
4634  bstrins_d(sp, zero_reg, std::log2(frame_alignment) - 1, 0);
4635  St_d(scratch, MemOperand(sp, stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
4636  } else {
4637  Sub_d(sp, sp, Operand(stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
4638  }
4639 }
4640 
4641 void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
4642  Register scratch) {
4643  PrepareCallCFunction(num_reg_arguments, 0, scratch);
4644 }

4646 int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(ExternalReference function,
4647  int num_reg_arguments,
4648  int num_double_arguments,
4649  SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
4650  Label* return_location) {

4653  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);

4655  li(scratch, function);
4656  return CallCFunctionHelper(scratch, num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments,
4657  set_isolate_data_slots, return_location);
4658 }

4682 
4683 int MacroAssembler::CallCFunctionHelper(
4684  Register function, int num_reg_arguments, int num_double_arguments,
4685  SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots, Label* return_location) {
4686  DCHECK_LE(num_reg_arguments + num_double_arguments, kMaxCParameters);
4687  DCHECK(has_frame());
4688 
4689  Label get_pc;
4690  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4691  // We're doing a C call, which means non-parameter caller-saved registers
4692  // (a0-a7, t0-t8) will be clobbered and so are available to use as scratches.
4693  // In the worst-case scenario, we'll need 2 scratch registers. We pick 3
4694  // registers minus the `function` register, in case `function` aliases with
4695  // any of the registers.
4696  temps.Include({t0, t1, t2, function});
4697  temps.Exclude(function);
4698 
4699  // Make sure that the stack is aligned before calling a C function unless
4700  // running in the simulator. The simulator has its own alignment check which
4701  // provides more information.
4702 #if V8_HOST_ARCH_LOONG64
4703  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4704  int frame_alignment = base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
4705  int frame_alignment_mask = frame_alignment - 1;
4706  if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
4707  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
4708  Label alignment_as_expected;
4709  {
4710  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4711  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4712  And(scratch, sp, Operand(frame_alignment_mask));
4713  Branch(&alignment_as_expected, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
4714  }
4715  // Don't use Check here, as it will call Runtime_Abort possibly
4716  // re-entering here.
4717  stop();
4718  bind(&alignment_as_expected);
4719  }
4720  }
4721 #endif // V8_HOST_ARCH_LOONG64
4722 
4723  // Just call directly. The function called cannot cause a GC, or
4724  // allow preemption, so the return address in the link register
4725  // stays correct.
4726  {
4727  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4728  if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
4729  // Save the frame pointer and PC so that the stack layout remains
4730  // iterable, even without an ExitFrame which normally exists between JS
4731  // and C frames.
4732  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4733  Register pc_scratch = temps.Acquire();
4734  DCHECK(!AreAliased(pc_scratch, function));
4735  CHECK(root_array_available());
4736 
4737  LoadLabelRelative(pc_scratch, &get_pc);
4738 
4739  St_d(pc_scratch,
4740  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerPC));
4741  St_d(fp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
4742  }
4743 
4744  int call_pc_offset;
4745  {
4746  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4747  Call(function);
4748  call_pc_offset = pc_offset();
4749  bind(&get_pc);
4750  if (return_location) bind(return_location);
4751 
4752  int before_offset = pc_offset();
4753  int stack_passed_arguments =
4754  CalculateStackPassedWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
4755 
4756  if (base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment() > kSystemPointerSize) {
4757  Ld_d(sp, MemOperand(sp, stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
4758  } else {
4759  Add_d(sp, sp, Operand(stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
4760  }
4761 
4762  if (kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall > pc_offset() - before_offset) {
4763  nop();
4764  }
4765  // We assume that with the nop padding, the move instruction uses
4766  // kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall bytes. When we patch in the deopt
4767  // trampoline, we patch it in after the move instruction, so that the
4768  // stack has been restored correctly.
4769  CHECK_EQ(kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall, pc_offset() - before_offset);
4770  }
4771 
4772  if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
4773  // We don't unset the PC; the FP is the source of truth.
4774  St_d(zero_reg,
4775  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
4776  }
4777 
4778  set_pc_for_safepoint();
4779 
4780  return call_pc_offset;
4781  }
4782 }
4783 
4784 #undef BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK
4785 
4786 void MacroAssembler::CheckPageFlag(Register object, int mask, Condition cc,
4787  Label* condition_met) {
4788  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4789  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4790  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4791  And(scratch, object, Operand(~MemoryChunk::GetAlignmentMaskForAssembler()));
4792  Ld_d(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset()));
4793  And(scratch, scratch, Operand(mask));
4794  Branch(condition_met, cc, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
4795 }
4796 
4797 Register GetRegisterThatIsNotOneOf(Register reg1, Register reg2, Register reg3,
4798  Register reg4, Register reg5,
4799  Register reg6) {
4800  RegList regs = {reg1, reg2, reg3, reg4, reg5, reg6};
4801 
4802  const RegisterConfiguration* config = RegisterConfiguration::Default();
4803  for (int i = 0; i < config->num_allocatable_general_registers(); ++i) {
4804  int code = config->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(i);
4805  Register candidate = Register::from_code(code);
4806  if (regs.has(candidate)) continue;
4807  return candidate;
4808  }
4809  UNREACHABLE();
4810 }

4812 void MacroAssembler::ComputeCodeStartAddress(Register dst) {
4813  // TODO(LOONG_dev): range check, add Pcadd macro function?
4814  pcaddi(dst, -pc_offset() >> 2);
4815 }
4816 
4817 // Check if the code object is marked for deoptimization. If it is, then it
4818 // jumps to the CompileLazyDeoptimizedCode builtin. In order to do this we need
4819 // to:
4820 // 1. read from memory the word that contains that bit, which can be found in
4821 // the flags in the referenced {Code} object;
4822 // 2. test kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit in those flags; and
4823 // 3. if it is not zero then it jumps to the builtin.
4824 //
4825 // Note: With leaptiering we simply assert the code is not deoptimized.
4826 void MacroAssembler::BailoutIfDeoptimized() {
4827  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4828  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4829  if (v8_flags.debug_code || !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL) {
4830  int offset =
4831  InstructionStream::kCodeOffset - InstructionStream::kHeaderSize;
4832  LoadProtectedPointerField(
4833  scratch, MemOperand(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister, offset));
4834  Ld_wu(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Code::kFlagsOffset));
4835  }
4836 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4837  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4838  Label not_deoptimized;
4839  And(scratch, scratch, Operand(1 << Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit));
4840  Branch(&not_deoptimized, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
4841  Abort(AbortReason::kInvalidDeoptimizedCode);
4842  bind(&not_deoptimized);
4843  }
4844 #else
4845  And(scratch, scratch, Operand(1 << Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit));
4846  TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCompileLazyDeoptimizedCode, ne, scratch,
4847  Operand(zero_reg));
4848 #endif
4849 }
4850 
4851 void MacroAssembler::CallForDeoptimization(Builtin target, int, Label* exit,
4852  DeoptimizeKind kind, Label* ret,
4853  Label*) {
4854  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4855  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4856  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4857  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4858  Ld_d(scratch,
4859  MemOperand(kRootRegister, IsolateData::BuiltinEntrySlotOffset(target)));
4860  Call(scratch);
4861  DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(exit),
4862  (kind == DeoptimizeKind::kLazy) ? Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize
4863  : Deoptimizer::kEagerDeoptExitSize);
4864 }

4877 #endif

4888  JumpMode jump_mode) {

4891  // and callee agree on the signature (i.e. parameter count)?

4898 void MacroAssembler::CallJSFunction(Register function_object,
4899  uint16_t argument_count) {
4900  Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
4901 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4902  Register dispatch_handle = kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister;
4903  Register parameter_count = s1;
4904  Register scratch = s2;
4905 
4906  Ld_w(dispatch_handle,
4907  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
4908  LoadEntrypointAndParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(code, parameter_count,
4909  dispatch_handle, scratch);
4910 
4911  // Force a safe crash if the parameter count doesn't match.
4912  SbxCheck(le, AbortReason::kJSSignatureMismatch, parameter_count,
4913  Operand(argument_count));
4914  Call(code);
4915 #else
4916  CHECK(!V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
4917  LoadTaggedField(code,
4918  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
4919  CallCodeObject(code, kJSEntrypointTag);
4920 #endif
4921 }
4922 
4923 #if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4924 void MacroAssembler::CallJSDispatchEntry(JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
4925  uint16_t argument_count) {
4926  Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
4927  Register scratch = s1;
4928  li(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister,
4929  Operand(dispatch_handle.value(), RelocInfo::JS_DISPATCH_HANDLE));
4930  // WARNING: This entrypoint load is only safe because we are storing a
4931  // RelocInfo for the dispatch handle in the li above (thus keeping the
4932  // dispatch entry alive) _and_ because the entrypoints are not compactable
4933  // (thus meaning that the calculation in the entrypoint load is not
4934  // invalidated by a compaction).
4935  // TODO(leszeks): Make this less of a footgun.
4936  static_assert(!JSDispatchTable::kSupportsCompaction);
4937  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(code, dispatch_handle, scratch);
4938  CHECK_EQ(argument_count,
4939  IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->GetParameterCount(
4940  dispatch_handle));
4941  Call(code);
4942 }
4943 #endif

4945 void MacroAssembler::JumpJSFunction(Register function_object,
4946  JumpMode jump_mode) {
4947  CHECK(!V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
4948 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4949  // This implementation is not currently used because callers usually need
4950  // to load both entry point and parameter count and then do something with
4951  // the latter before the actual call.
4952  UNREACHABLE();
4953 #else
4954  Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
4955  LoadTaggedField(code,
4956  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
4957  JumpCodeObject(code, kJSEntrypointTag, jump_mode);
4958 #endif
4959 }

4962 
4963 void MacroAssembler::ResolveWasmCodePointer(Register target,
4964  uint64_t signature_hash) {
4965  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4966  ExternalReference global_jump_table =
4967  ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table();
4968  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4969  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4970  li(scratch, global_jump_table);
4971 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
4972  static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == 16);
4973  Alsl_d(target, target, scratch, 4);
4974  Ld_d(scratch,
4975  MemOperand(target, wasm::WasmCodePointerTable::kOffsetOfSignatureHash));
4976  bool has_second_tmp = temps.hasAvailable();
4977  Register signature_hash_register = has_second_tmp ? temps.Acquire() : target;
4978  if (!has_second_tmp) {
4979  Push(signature_hash_register);
4980  }
4981  li(signature_hash_register, Operand(signature_hash));
4982  SbxCheck(Condition::kEqual, AbortReason::kWasmSignatureMismatch, scratch,
4983  Operand(signature_hash_register));
4984  if (!has_second_tmp) {
4985  Pop(signature_hash_register);
4986  }
4987 #else
4988  static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == 8);
4989  Alsl_d(target, target, scratch, 3);
4990 #endif
4991 
4992  Ld_d(target, MemOperand(target, 0));
4993 }
4994 
4995 void MacroAssembler::CallWasmCodePointer(Register target,
4996  uint64_t signature_hash,
4997  CallJumpMode call_jump_mode) {
4998  ResolveWasmCodePointer(target, signature_hash);
4999  if (call_jump_mode == CallJumpMode::kTailCall) {
5000  Jump(target);
5001  } else {
5002  Call(target);
5003  }
5004 }

5006 void MacroAssembler::CallWasmCodePointerNoSignatureCheck(Register target) {
5007  ExternalReference global_jump_table =
5008  ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table();
5009  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5010  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5011  li(scratch, global_jump_table);
5012  constexpr unsigned int kEntrySizeLog2 =
5013  std::bit_width(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry)) - 1;
5014  Alsl_d(target, target, scratch, kEntrySizeLog2);
5015  Ld_d(target, MemOperand(target, 0));
5016 
5017  Call(target);
5018 }

5027 namespace {
5028 
5029 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5030 // Only used when leaptiering is disabled.
5031 void TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(MacroAssembler* masm,
5032  Register optimized_code_entry) {
5033  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
5034  // -- a0 : actual argument count
5035  // -- a3 : new target (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
5036  // -- a1 : target function (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
5037  // -----------------------------------
5038  DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code_entry, a1, a3));
5039 
5040  Label heal_optimized_code_slot;
5041 
5042  // If the optimized code is cleared, go to runtime to update the optimization
5043  // marker field.
5044  __ LoadWeakValue(optimized_code_entry, optimized_code_entry,
5045  &heal_optimized_code_slot);
5046 
5047  // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
5048  __ LoadCodePointerField(
5049  optimized_code_entry,
5050  FieldMemOperand(optimized_code_entry, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset));
5051 
5052  // Check if the optimized code is marked for deopt. If it is, call the
5053  // runtime to clear it.
5054  __ TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimizationAndJump(optimized_code_entry, a6, ne,
5055  &heal_optimized_code_slot);
5056 
5057  // Optimized code is good, get it into the closure and link the closure into
5058  // the optimized functions list, then tail call the optimized code.
5059  // The feedback vector is no longer used, so reuse it as a scratch
5060  // register.
5061  __ ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(optimized_code_entry, a1);
5062 
5063  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == a2, "ABI mismatch");
5064  __ LoadCodeInstructionStart(a2, optimized_code_entry, kJSEntrypointTag);
5065  __ Jump(a2);
5066 
5067  // Optimized code slot contains deoptimized code or code is cleared and
5068  // optimized code marker isn't updated. Evict the code, update the marker
5069  // and re-enter the closure's code.
5070  __ bind(&heal_optimized_code_slot);
5071  __ GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kHealOptimizedCodeSlot);
5072 }
5073 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5074 
5075 } // namespace

5083  }

5094 void MacroAssembler::ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(
5095  Register optimized_code, Register closure) {
5096  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5097  DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code, closure));
5098 
5099 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5100  UNREACHABLE();
5101 #else
5102  // Store code entry in the closure.
5103  StoreCodePointerField(optimized_code,
5104  FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
5105  RecordWriteField(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset, optimized_code,
5106  kRAHasNotBeenSaved, SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore, SmiCheck::kOmit,
5107  SlotDescriptor::ForCodePointerSlot());
5108 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5109 }
5110 
5111 void MacroAssembler::GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(
5112  Runtime::FunctionId function_id) {
5113  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5114  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
5115  // -- a0 : actual argument count (preserved for callee)
5116  // -- a1 : target function (preserved for callee)
5117  // -- a3 : new target (preserved for callee)
5118  // -- a4 : dispatch handle (preserved for callee)
5119  // -----------------------------------
5120  {
5121  FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
5122  // Push a copy of the target function, the new target, the actual
5123  // argument count, and the dispatch handle.
5124  // Push function as parameter to the runtime call.
5125  SmiTag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
5126  Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
5127  kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
5128 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
5129  // No need to SmiTag since dispatch handles always look like Smis.
5130  static_assert(kJSDispatchHandleShift > 0);
5131  AssertSmi(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
5132  Push(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
5133 #endif
5134  // Function is also the parameter to the runtime call.
5135  Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
5136 
5137  CallRuntime(function_id, 1);
5138  LoadCodeInstructionStart(a2, a0, kJSEntrypointTag);
5139 
5140  // Restore target function, new target, actual argument count and dispatch
5141  // handle.
5142 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
5143  Pop(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
5144 #endif
5145  Pop(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
5146  kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
5147  SmiUntag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
5148  }
5149 
5150  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == a2, "ABI mismatch");
5151  Jump(a2);
5152 }

5156 // Read off the flags in the feedback vector and check if there
5157 // is optimized code or a tiering state that needs to be processed.
5158 void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVectorFlagsAndJumpIfNeedsProcessing(
5159  Register flags, Register feedback_vector, CodeKind current_code_kind,
5160  Label* flags_need_processing) {
5161  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5162  Register scratch = t2;
5163  DCHECK(!AreAliased(t2, flags, feedback_vector));
5164  DCHECK(CodeKindCanTierUp(current_code_kind));
5165  uint32_t flag_mask =
5166  FeedbackVector::FlagMaskForNeedsProcessingCheckFrom(current_code_kind);
5167  Ld_hu(flags, FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset));
5168  And(scratch, flags, Operand(flag_mask));
5169  Branch(flags_need_processing, ne, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5170 }
5171 
5172 void MacroAssembler::OptimizeCodeOrTailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(
5173  Register flags, Register feedback_vector) {
5174  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5175  DCHECK(!AreAliased(flags, feedback_vector));
5176  Label maybe_has_optimized_code, maybe_needs_logging;
5177  // Check if optimized code marker is available.
5178  {
5179  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5180  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5181  And(scratch, flags,
5182  Operand(FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested));
5183  Branch(&maybe_needs_logging, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5184  }
5185 
5186  GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kCompileOptimized);
5187 
5188  bind(&maybe_needs_logging);
5189  {
5190  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5191  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5192  And(scratch, flags, Operand(FeedbackVector::LogNextExecutionBit::kMask));
5193  Branch(&maybe_has_optimized_code, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5194  }
5195 
5196  GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kFunctionLogNextExecution);
5197 
5198  bind(&maybe_has_optimized_code);
5199  Register optimized_code_entry = flags;
5200  LoadTaggedField(optimized_code_entry,
5201  FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
5202  FeedbackVector::kMaybeOptimizedCodeOffset));
5203 
5204  TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(this, optimized_code_entry);
5205 }
5206 
5207 #endif // !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING

5210  const MemOperand& field_operand) {

5212  DecompressTagged(destination, field_operand);
5213  } else {
5214  Ld_d(destination, field_operand);
5215  }
5216 }

5239 void MacroAssembler::AtomicStoreTaggedField(Register src,
5240  const MemOperand& dst) {

5242  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5243  Add_d(scratch, dst.base(), dst.offset());
5244  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
5245  amswap_db_w(zero_reg, src, scratch);
5246  } else {
5247  amswap_db_d(zero_reg, src, scratch);
5248  }

5251 void MacroAssembler::DecompressTaggedSigned(Register dst,
5252  const MemOperand& src) {
5253  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5254  Ld_wu(dst, src);
5255  if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
5256  // Corrupt the top 32 bits. Made up of 16 fixed bits and 16 pc offset bits.
5257  Add_d(dst, dst, ((kDebugZapValue << 16) | (pc_offset() & 0xffff)) << 32);
5258  }
5259 }

5265 }

5278 void MacroAssembler::DecompressProtected(const Register& destination,
5279  const MemOperand& field_operand) {
5280 #if V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5281  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5282  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5283  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5284  Ld_wu(destination, field_operand);
5285  Ld_d(scratch,
5286  MemOperand(kRootRegister, IsolateData::trusted_cage_base_offset()));
5287  Or(destination, destination, scratch);
5288 #else
5289  UNREACHABLE();
5290 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5291 }

5293 void MacroAssembler::AtomicDecompressTaggedSigned(Register dst,
5294  const MemOperand& src) {
5295  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5296  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5297  Ld_wu(dst, src);
5298  dbar(0);
5299  if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
5300  // Corrupt the top 32 bits. Made up of 16 fixed bits and 16 pc offset bits.
5301  Add_d(dst, dst, ((kDebugZapValue << 16) | (pc_offset() & 0xffff)) << 32);
5302  }
5303 }

5305 int MacroAssembler::AtomicDecompressTagged(Register dst,
5306  const MemOperand& src) {
5307  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5308  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5309  Ld_wu(dst, src);
5310  int pc_offset_of_load = pc_offset() - kInstrSize;
5311  dbar(0);
5312  Add_d(dst, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister, dst);
5313  return pc_offset_of_load;
5314 }
5315 
5316 // Calls an API function. Allocates HandleScope, extracts returned value
5317 // from handle and propagates exceptions. Clobbers C argument registers
5318 // and C caller-saved registers. Restores context. On return removes
5319 // (*argc_operand + slots_to_drop_on_return) * kSystemPointerSize
5320 // (GCed, includes the call JS arguments space and the additional space
5321 // allocated for the fast call).
5322 void CallApiFunctionAndReturn(MacroAssembler* masm, bool with_profiling,
5323  Register function_address,
5324  ExternalReference thunk_ref, Register thunk_arg,
5325  int slots_to_drop_on_return,
5326  MemOperand* argc_operand,
5327  MemOperand return_value_operand) {
5328  using ER = ExternalReference;
5329 
5330  Isolate* isolate = masm->isolate();
5331  MemOperand next_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5332  ER::handle_scope_next_address(isolate), no_reg);
5333  MemOperand limit_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5334  ER::handle_scope_limit_address(isolate), no_reg);
5335  MemOperand level_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5336  ER::handle_scope_level_address(isolate), no_reg);
5337 
5338  Register return_value = a0;
5339  Register scratch = a4;
5340  Register scratch2 = a5;
5341 
5342  // Allocate HandleScope in callee-saved registers.
5343  // We will need to restore the HandleScope after the call to the API function,
5344  // by allocating it in callee-saved registers it'll be preserved by C code.
5345  Register prev_next_address_reg = s0;
5346  Register prev_limit_reg = s1;
5347  Register prev_level_reg = s2;
5348 
5349  // C arguments (kCArgRegs[0/1]) are expected to be initialized outside, so
5350  // this function must not corrupt them (return_value overlaps with
5351  // kCArgRegs[0] but that's ok because we start using it only after the C
5352  // call).
5353  DCHECK(!AreAliased(kCArgRegs[0], kCArgRegs[1], // C args
5354  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
5355  // function_address and thunk_arg might overlap but this function must not
5356  // corrupted them until the call is made (i.e. overlap with return_value is
5357  // fine).
5358  DCHECK(!AreAliased(function_address, // incoming parameters
5359  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
5360  DCHECK(!AreAliased(thunk_arg, // incoming parameters
5361  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
5362  {
5363  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
5364  "Allocate HandleScope in callee-save registers.");
5365  __ Ld_d(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
5366  __ Ld_d(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
5367  __ Ld_w(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
5368  __ Add_w(scratch, prev_level_reg, Operand(1));
5369  __ St_w(scratch, level_mem_op);
5370  }
5371 
5372  Label profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, done_api_call;
5373  if (with_profiling) {
5374  __ RecordComment("Check if profiler or side effects check is enabled");
5375  __ Ld_b(scratch,
5376  __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kExecutionMode));
5377  __ Branch(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, ne, scratch,
5378  Operand(zero_reg));
5379 #ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
5380  __ RecordComment("Check if RCS is enabled");
5381  __ li(scratch, ER::address_of_runtime_stats_flag());
5382  __ Ld_w(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
5383  __ Branch(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, ne, scratch,
5384  Operand(zero_reg));
5385 #endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
5386  }
5387 
5388  __ RecordComment("Call the api function directly.");
5389  __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(function_address);
5390  __ bind(&done_api_call);
5391 
5392  Label propagate_exception;
5393  Label delete_allocated_handles;
5394  Label leave_exit_frame;
5395 
5396  __ RecordComment("Load the value from ReturnValue");
5397  __ Ld_d(return_value, return_value_operand);
5398 
5399  {
5400  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
5401  masm,
5402  "No more valid handles (the result handle was the last one)."
5403  "Restore previous handle scope.");
5404  __ St_d(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
5405  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5406  __ Ld_w(scratch, level_mem_op);
5407  __ Sub_w(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
5408  __ Check(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedLevelAfterReturnFromApiCall, scratch,
5409  Operand(prev_level_reg));
5410  }
5411  __ St_w(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
5412  __ Ld_d(scratch, limit_mem_op);
5413  __ Branch(&delete_allocated_handles, ne, prev_limit_reg, Operand(scratch));
5414  }
5415 
5416  __ RecordComment("Leave the API exit frame.");
5417  __ bind(&leave_exit_frame);
5418 
5419  Register argc_reg = prev_limit_reg;
5420  if (argc_operand != nullptr) {
5421  // Load the number of stack slots to drop before LeaveExitFrame modifies sp.
5422  __ Ld_d(argc_reg, *argc_operand);
5423  }
5424 
5425  __ LeaveExitFrame(scratch);
5426 
5427  {
5428  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
5429  "Check if the function scheduled an exception.");
5430  __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
5431  __ Ld_d(scratch2, __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5432  ER::exception_address(isolate), no_reg));
5433  __ Branch(&propagate_exception, ne, scratch, Operand(scratch2));
5434  }
5435 
5436  __ AssertJSAny(return_value, scratch, scratch2,
5437  AbortReason::kAPICallReturnedInvalidObject);
5438 
5439  if (argc_operand == nullptr) {
5440  DCHECK_NE(slots_to_drop_on_return, 0);
5441  __ Add_d(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
5442  } else {
5443  // {argc_operand} was loaded into {argc_reg} above.
5444  if (slots_to_drop_on_return != 0) {
5445  __ Add_d(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
5446  }
5447  __ Alsl_d(sp, argc_reg, sp, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5448  }
5449 
5450  __ Ret();
5451 
5452  if (with_profiling) {
5453  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Call the api function via thunk wrapper.");
5454  __ bind(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
5455  // Additional parameter is the address of the actual callback function.
5456  if (thunk_arg.is_valid()) {
5457  MemOperand thunk_arg_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5458  IsolateFieldId::kApiCallbackThunkArgument);
5459  __ St_d(thunk_arg, thunk_arg_mem_op);
5460  }
5461  __ li(scratch, thunk_ref);
5462  __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(scratch);
5463  __ Branch(&done_api_call);
5464  }
5465 
5466  __ RecordComment("An exception was thrown. Propagate it.");
5467  __ bind(&propagate_exception);
5468  __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kPropagateException);
5469 
5470  {
5471  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
5472  masm, "HandleScope limit has changed. Delete allocated extensions.");
5473  __ bind(&delete_allocated_handles);
5474  __ St_d(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
5475  // Save the return value in a callee-save register.
5476  Register saved_result = prev_limit_reg;
5477  __ mov(saved_result, a0);
5478  __ PrepareCallCFunction(1, prev_level_reg);
5479  __ li(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address());
5480  __ CallCFunction(ER::delete_handle_scope_extensions(), 1);
5481  __ mov(kCArgRegs[0], saved_result);
5482  __ jmp(&leave_exit_frame);
5483  }
5484 }
5485 
5486 } // namespace internal
5487 } // namespace v8
5488

5490
